Never commit cache files or directories to git.

**Why:** User explicitly requested. Cache files are local artifacts that don't belong in version control.

**How to apply:** When staging files for a commit, exclude any files or directories named "cache" or containing cache data (e.g., `__pycache__`, `.cache`, `node_modules/.cache`, etc.).
